Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyday as a consumer, you interact with and perform minor miracles \N 作为消费者，你每天都在与一些小小的奇迹打交道
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.44,0:00:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet you probably don't recognize them as such \N 不过你可能并不这样看
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about them at all, you might consider them as nuisances or as obstacles \N 当你念及它们时，你可能还会觉得它们是种妨碍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.52,0:00:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But while they're largely unappreciated \N 不过虽然它们不受待见
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.52,0:00:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,these small things actually make our modern lives possible \N 现代生活却有赖于这些小东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I talking about? Prices \N 我在说什么？价格
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the prices we pay everyday for goods and services \N 就是我们每天为商品和服务支付的那个“价格”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You might think they're just the unfortunate cost of getting something you want \N 你可能会觉得价格就是为了获取某物而不幸不得不支付的成本
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.38,0:00:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're much more than that \N 但其实远不止如此
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.78,0:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you learn about the vast amount of information contained within every price \N 当你明白了价格背后蕴含着海量的信息后
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.00,0:00:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,each one becomes a marvel \N 它们就变成了奇迹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a wonder that helps coordinate the billions of choices of multitudes of people \N 一个能够将大众数以亿级的不同选择组织进
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,into a productive and dynamic economy \N 一个富有生产力的动态经济体的奇迹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.46,0:00:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain \N 让我接着说明一下
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.28,0:00:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about, say, ketchup \N 以番茄酱为例
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.28,0:00:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the primary ingredient in that delicious red source is, of course, tomatoes \N 它的主要成分当然就是番茄
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.38,0:00:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now suppose there is a terrible draught in California \N 现在假设加州发生了严重的干旱
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.26,0:00:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,this year's tomato harvest drops substantially \N 导致今年的番茄产量严重下降
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.34,0:00:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The demand is still there \N 但人们对番茄酱的需求却没变
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.96,0:01:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,people still want ketchup as much as they did before for there hamburgers and fries \N 大家在吃汉堡薯条时依然想配那么多的番茄酱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.10,0:01:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but the supply is shriveled \N 但供应萎缩了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so farmers start to charge higher prices for their tomatoes \N 所以农民开始以更高的价格出售番茄
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that means ketchup makers have to pay more for tomatoes \N 这意味着番茄酱生产商需要花更多的钱购买番茄
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.26,0:01:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so they charge grocery stores more for their product \N 所以他们对下游零售商收取更高的价格
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.90,0:01:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and so in turn grocery stores charge higher prices for ketchup to consumers \N 最终零售商向消费者出售的番茄酱更贵了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.78,0:01:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The important point here is just how customers responds \N 这里的要点在于消费者如何回应
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.92,0:01:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A few of them won't care much about the higher price \N 一小部分消费者不会在意涨价
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.06,0:01:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll continue to buy as many bottles of ketchup as before \N 他们会购买像往常一样多的番茄酱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.18,0:01:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but most consumers will care \N 不过大部分消费者会在意涨价
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.42,0:01:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they will switch to mayonnaise or to mustard \N 他们会转向蛋黄酱或者芥末酱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.38,0:01:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or just go without condiments altogether \N 或者干脆就不用佐料了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.12,0:01:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's actually a good outcome given the draught \N 考虑到干旱带来的减产，这其实是我们乐见的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.30,0:01:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There simply aren't as many tomatoes to go around as before \N 因为市面上就没有像以前那么多的番茄在流通
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,People as a group need to eat fewer tomatoes \N 所以整个社会需要减少番茄的消费量
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.36,0:01:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and this uptake in the price of ketchup leads some people \N 而番茄酱价格的上涨正好让那些
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.68,0:01:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,those who care the least about the particular condiment to use less of it \N 对番茄酱最不在意的人少吃一些番茄酱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and that means total consumption of tomatoes shrinks \N 从而减少了对番茄的总需求
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.72,0:01:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,From a bird's eye view \N 从火星人的角度来看
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it might look as though this chain of events is consciously coordinated \N 这一连串事件似乎是精心组织的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.38,0:02:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that the farmer, manufacturer, grocery stores, and customers \N 农民、厂商、零售店、消费者
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.82,0:02:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,are all working together according to some plan or to some directive \N 似乎是在某种计划或指示下共同合作
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.52,0:02:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to adjust to the fact that the draught destroyed a lot of tomatoes \N 以应对干旱带来的番茄减产
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.88,0:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course we know there aren't \N 但当然我们知道并没有这样的计划和指示
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.58,0:02:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no bureau of condiments ordering people to hold the ketchup \N 并没有一个调味料管理局命令人们少吃番茄酱
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.26,0:02:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Information about the need to cut back tomato consumption \N 人们需要减少番茄酱消费的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.36,0:02:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was communicated organically through prices \N 是通过价格有机传导的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.04,0:02:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Or as the great economist Friedrich Hayek put it \N 或者如伟大的经济学家弗雷德里希·哈耶克所表述的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.04,0:02:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the ketchup price is, quote, a kind of machinery for registering change, unquote \N 番茄酱价格是一种“体现变化的机制”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.16,0:02:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now multiply this chain of events by trillions \N 如果把这一串事件乘以万亿
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.80,0:02:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the world of economy \N 那就是全球经济
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.36,0:02:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There are billions of buyers and suppliers adjusting in real time, every hour of every day \N 数以亿计的买家和卖家每时每刻针对着短缺和富余
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.04,0:02:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to shortages and surpluses \N 不停地做着实时调整
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.04,0:02:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're elaborately coordinating their behavior with each other \N 他们精巧地协调彼此的行为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.96,0:02:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and adjust to on the ground developments \N 并适应眼前的变化
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.96,0:02:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don't even realize \N 他们甚至都没有意识到
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they're part of this great global chain of cooperation \N 他们是这个了不起的全球合作链的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.32,0:02:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this coordination and adjustment is thanks to prices \N 这一切协调与调整都要归功于价格
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.02,0:03:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all those different bits of information conveyed in that one little number \N 这个小小的数字传递着所有这些不同的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about that next time you go to grocery store \N 下次去杂货店的时候记得想想这事
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.40,0:03:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We understand the power of prices thanks to economists like Friedrich Hayek \N 我们对价格的理解要归功于哈耶克这样的经济学家
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To learn more about Hayek's essential ideas \N 想了解哈耶克的更多重要思想
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.32,0:03:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they help explain our world \N 以及它们是怎么解释这个世界的
